Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All measured parameters are within or close to normal ranges. HbA1c is at the upper limit, suggesting good but borderline glycemic control. Creatinine is slightly below normal but not clinically significant. Lipid profile is favorable, with LDL and triglycerides well controlled and HDL at the lower normal limit. No acute abnormalities detected. Recommend continued monitoring, especially of glycemic control.
